houseWallet().notice: optional sink / profit address for later use

playBlackjack(uint256,uint256).notice: Single-step blackjack (no split/double, no multi-hit UI yet): - We auto play both player & dealer with standard rules:    Player hits to 17 or more.    Dealer hits to 17 or more. - Payout:    Player natural blackjack vs non-blackjack dealer : 2.5x    Normal win                                      : 1.95x    Push                                            : 1.0x    Loss                                            : 0x Frontend can still decorate with cards using the random stream.

playCoinFlip(uint256,uint256,bool).notice: betType: guessHeads = true => heads, false => tails house edge comes from 1.98x < 2.00x

playDice(uint256,uint256,uint8).notice: Simple 2d6 dice: betType:   0 = OVER 7  (sum >= 8)   -> ~15/36   1 = UNDER 7 (sum <= 6)   -> ~15/36   2 = EXACT 7 (sum == 7)   -> 6/36 multipliers:   over/under: 2.20x gross => 220   exact 7   : 5.50x gross => 550

playHiLo(uint256,uint256,bool).notice: Simple single-step Hi-Lo: - contract draws two ranks in [2..14] (2..10,J,Q,K,A) - you guess if NEXT is higher or lower than FIRST - ties push (1.0x)

playJackpotSpin(uint256,uint256).notice: Jackpot wheel segments (by index 0..11), examples:   [ 0x, 1x, 2x, 3x, 5x, 10x, 15x, 20x, 25x, 50x, 75x, 100x ] using broad probabilities via modulo.

playMine(uint256,uint256,uint8).notice: Simple risk-based mine game: - riskLevel 1 (low):   70% 1.5x, 20% 2x, 10% 0x - riskLevel 2 (mid):   55% 2x,   25% 3x, 20% 0x - riskLevel 3 (high):  40% 3x,   20% 5x, 40% 0x Frontend can map riskLevel to grid / picks theme; on-chain we just resolve a single tiered outcome.

playPan(uint256,uint256).notice: Pan wheel (simple multiplier buckets): rnd in [0..999]:   0549   : 0x (dry pan)   550799 : 2x   800919 : 5x   920969 : 10x   970989 : 20x   990997 : 50x   998999 : 100x

playRoulette(uint256,uint256,uint8,uint8.notice: betType:   0 = straight (number in 036 via `number`)   1 = RED   2 = BLACK   3 = EVEN   4 = ODD For straight: 35:1 net, 36x gross => 3600 For even money bets: ~1.96x gross => 196

playSlots(uint256,uint256).notice: 3x3 grid, 5 paylines (3 rows + 2 diagonals). We use a simple paytable:   Index 0 (BGLD coin): triple 40x, pair 3x   Index 1 (nugget)   : triple 25x, pair 2.2x   Index 2 (pickaxe)  : triple 15x, pair 2.0x   Index 3 (cart)     : triple 10x, pair 1.8x   Index 4 (lantern)  : triple 6x,  pair 1.5x   Index 5 (BAR)      : triple 3x,  pair 1.3x We sum all paying lines but cap via gameMaxMultiplier.

playVideoPoker(uint256,uint256).notice: Single-step Jacks or Better: - We draw 5 cards (ranks 2..14, suits 0..3). - Frontend can reconstruct from tx hash if desired. Payout table (gross multipliers):   Royal Flush       : 50x   Straight Flush    : 40x   Four of a Kind    : 25x   Full House        : 9x   Flush             : 6x   Straight          : 4x   Three of a Kind   : 3x   Two Pair          : 2x   Jacks or Better   : 1.5x

playWar(uint256,uint256).notice: High card vs dealer: - Draw player + dealer ranks 2..14 - Higher rank wins 1.95x gross - Tie pushes (1.0x)
